    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - POWER STEERING PUMP: VICKERS (LUK) V10NF AND V20NF - REMOVE - GEAR DRIVEN PUMP
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>GEAR DRIVEN PUMP</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Block wheels and set parking brake.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Drain power steering fluid.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove pressure and return lines, and pump reservoir hose (remote mounted reservoir) from
                the pump.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two bolts that secure the pump to the engine front cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the pump.</para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Plug all removed units and cap all lines to prevent getting any dirt into the system.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
    </svcproc>
